# StatRoute Core Patterns

You are a Senior Systems Architect implementing StatRoute ‚Äî a FastAPI emergency supply routing engine. These rules are non-negotiable.

## EventBus
- Always import from `app.bus`: `from app.bus import event_bus`
- Never define `asyncio.Queue()` inline anywhere
- Push events with `await event_bus.put({"type": "...", ...})`
  > WHY: All producers and the SSE consumer share one queue. Inline queues break the pipeline silently.

## Redis Access
- Always access via `request.app.state.redis` inside route handlers
- Never import or instantiate `redis` directly in routers
  > WHY: The connection pool is initialized once in the lifespan hook. Direct imports create unclosed connections.

## App State (read-only at request time)
- `request.app.state.static_network_graph` ‚Äî `dict[str, dict[str, float]]`, loaded once at startup
- `request.app.state.hospital_node_map` ‚Äî `dict[str, str]`, name ‚Üí node key
- Never re-fetch these from Supabase during a request
  > WHY: O(1) lookup vs. network round-trip per request.

## Pydantic v2 (mandatory)
- `.model_dump()` ‚Äî not `.dict()`
- `model_validate()` ‚Äî not `parse_obj()`
- `Literal["Critical", "High", "Medium"]` for urgency ‚Äî never raw `str`
  > WHY: `.dict()` is deprecated in Pydantic v2 and will be removed. Using it produces warnings that pollute logs.

## Inventory Decrement Contract
- `decrement_inventory(supabase, supplier_id, item, qty) -> bool`
- Returns `False` if 0 rows updated (insufficient stock or concurrent depletion)
- Caller raises HTTP 409 on `False`
- NEVER subtract quantity in Python ‚Äî always via Supabase RPC `decrement_inventory`
  > WHY: Postgres row-lock prevents race conditions under concurrent load. Python-side arithmetic has TOCTOU vulnerability.

## Routing Pipeline Order (POST /api/emergency)
1. Parse with Gemini ‚Üí validate `EmergencyRequest`
2. Resolve `destination_node` from `hospital_node_map` ‚Üí 422 if missing
3. `sha256(hospital + item + urgency)` ‚Üí Redis GET
4. Cache HIT: try decrement ‚Üí if fails, evict key + fall through to MISS path
5. Cache MISS: `find_supplier` ‚Üí Dijkstra (circuit-protected) ‚Üí decrement ‚Üí Redis SET
6. `event_bus.put(route_dispatched)`

Never reorder steps 4 and 5. The stale eviction loop is intentional.

## Circuit Breaker
- `breaker.call(compute_path, ...)` ‚Äî sync call, pybreaker wraps synchronous Dijkstra
- On `CircuitBreakerError`: use `STATIC_FALLBACK_PATH`, capture to Sentry, push `circuit_open` event
- Inventory decrement ALWAYS runs after the try/except block, regardless of fallback
  > WHY: Physical supplies are real even when the map visualizer fails.

## Schema Separation
- `EmergencyInput` ‚Äî route parameter type (raw `message: str`)
- `EmergencyRequest` ‚Äî Gemini output schema (structured fields)
- Never use `EmergencyRequest` as a FastAPI route parameter
  > WHY: Conflating them causes FastAPI to reject raw text from the frontend.
